inatlantic</a> , <a href="https://twitter.com/THEHUNNABAND?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">@THEHUNNABAND</a> , <a href="https://twitter.com/hotmilkhotmilk?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">@hotmilkhotmilk</a> , <a href="https://twitter.com/frankturner?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">@frankturner</a> (playing Love Ire &amp; Song in full), mclusky, <a href="https://twitter.com/ladisputeband?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">@ladisputeband</a> (second set), <a href="https://twitter.com/frontiererband?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">@frontiererband</a> , Press Club, and a whole BUNCH more awesome bands are joining 2000trees 2025!! <a href="https://t.co/vKvpr5UmoI">pic.twitter.com/vKvpr5UmoI</a></p><p> — 2000trees Festival (@2000trees) <a href="https://twitter.com/2000trees/status/1907417967928778789?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">April 2, 2025</a> </p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><p> “Getting to watch the festival evolve and grow into something that truly connects with rock and alternative music fans in a way that gives them a sense of ownership of the festival is brilliant,” he added. “We always feel like because of that, we give it a bit extra when we play there and can&#39;t wait to get back on site and smash it with the ever-growing community this summer.”</p><p> Elsewhere, <a href="https://nme-next.netlify.app/artists/puppy">Puppy</a> will be returning to the site for their first show of 2025 and a festival exclusive, while Frank Turner also joins the line-up and will be playing a solo set for his sophomore album &#39;Love Ire &amp; Song&#39; on the Friday (July 11).</p><p> “Trees has been a home away from home for me since the early days, so I thought we could celebrate that together with a rendition of &#39;Love Ire &amp; Song&#39; in full on the Forest Stage,” Turner said. “I think it&#39;s going to be magic; see you there.”</p><p> Other new additions to the bill include Australian punk band <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/press-club">Press Club</a> 